# Rover Robotics ROS2 — Project Rules

- Four packages: driver, description, gazebo, input_manager. Build with colcon from a ROS 2 workspace.
- Copy existing robot launch + config pairs; do not invent new layout patterns.
- Driver executable: `roverrobotics_driver` (runtime node name often `roverrobotics`).
- `librover` is vendored under `roverrobotics_driver/library/librover/` — edit in-tree, not as external dep.
- Stable releases live on distro branches (`humble`, `jazzy`); `main` is active development.
- Minimize scope: no drive-by refactors, no unrelated formatting, no new markdown unless requested.
